5. Print it! You can print on your card stock or premium photo paper and set your printer’s settings to borderless, marginless or full bleed for 8.5” x 11” (or A4 for international customers) to ensure proper size. Change your output settings to High, Photo Print (matte paper) or your printer’s best print setup. This will ensure proper color output and crisp printing. I recommend using good quality 65lb- 110lb bright white matte card stock. Premium weight photo paper is another great option in matte or soft gloss Alternatively, save your file onto a USB stick and take to your local printer for professional printing.

6. Score along the score lines first then cut along the cut guides (you may want to use a straight edge and a blade to make the cut). Make sure all of the gray guides are cut away! Fold the sides of the envelope in put glue on the folds and then fold up the back and let dry.

7. Fold card and envelope flap and TA DA! A card and envelope!

results.title: And...You're How Old?
results.description:
And...You're How Old?

It was a beautiful Saturday afternoon and after spending most of the morning at my favorite discount books and magazines store, I carried 2 shopping bags filled with my favorite read- goods/literature:

Highlights for Children
Mad Magazines
The Far Side
Comic books
Pocket dictionaries, blank journals
and of course...Cause-mop-oliton

I sat quietly at the bus stop drinking my usual almond milk and giggling at the humorous and entertaining memes, picture puzzles and Alfred Newman’s “What...Me Worry?” funny captions.

My bus arrived too quickly and I started to scramble gathering my stack of magazines...clumsily dropping a couple of them.

A young couple started to assist me as tho I was some old woman who needed help crossing the street and even proceeded to direct me towards the elderly section at the front of the bus.

I smiled and politely said, 

“No, thanks guys.  Age is in the Mind of the Older.”

and happily walked to the back of the bus...sat down and continued to enjoy my read-goods.  :)

Esther Monsalve 
The Angel Shop 

p.s.  the items displayed are not for sale in this etsy posting...just the short story called,  And...You're How Old?

Thank you.

Note: Please use MEMO, an editor writing software, in oder to open this digital file.

Made from real book pages this artistic "Live Laugh Love and Read" sign is lovingly and uniquely crafted. No two are ever exactly alike. Do you want a different message and can't find it in my shop? No problem. Message me for a custom order and I can easily change the text or size.

You can decide whether you would prefer to hang it on the wall or use the dowel stand it on a book shelf, desk, or wherever you choose!

After receiving your order I will have your sign ready to ship in 7 days.

Carefully crafted and handmade from:
-High quality oak or pine boards
-Matte finish
-Letters cut carefully from real book pages. Yes, I found a way to recycle the old and worn out books in a special and timeless way.
-Sawtooth hanger
-Dowel

Sign Size: 24” X 5.5” X .75”

I have three styles available (see sample pictures)
1) "Gray" Oak aged with an eco-friendly solution to give it the gray appearance. Please note that oak boards respond differently to the solution so some will be lighter or darker than what appears.
2) Stained Oak with a beautiful Dark Walnut stain
3) Pine board with layered paint (white beneath with top layer dark brown) and textured to give it a distressed appearance

How long does it take to ship?
Because it is made to order it takes about 7 days to ship. My signs are truly unique and there are many steps that to go into them. I also want to make sure that they will last for a very long time and triple finish them. Between each coat I give them a full cure and then the final coat is left to cure for at least 3 days.

Custom:
